 to describe its intended action. I think that the term 'Update' is commonly understood to mean 'Update the application's view to reflect the state of the model' that 'Allow me to Update the values for this item'. In this way, it's closer to 'Refresh' than it is to 'Edit'.\n\nWouldn't it make more sense to change all uses of 'Update' to 'Edit'? And if an 'Edit' action is going to edit something other than the item's values, perhaps that should be clarified as well, as in 'Edit Setting Definition'?\n\nI'm posting this for discussion in http://forums.modx.com/thread/75425/ui-discrepancy-between-edit-and-update-actions\n","performed_via_github_app":null,"score":1.0},{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/modxcms/revolution/issues/15141","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/modxcms/revolution","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/modxcms/revolution/issues/15141/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/modxcms/revolution/issues/15141/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/modxcms/revolution/issues/15141/events","html_url":"https://github.com/modxcms/revolution/issues/15141","id":646874534,"node_id":"MDU6SXNzdWU2NDY4NzQ1MzQ=","number":15141,"title":"Unknown column 'modResource.alias_visible' in 'field list'","user":{"login":"Ibochkarev","id":2138260,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjIxMzgyNjA=","avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/2138260?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev","html_url":"https://github.com/Ibochkarev","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/Ibochkarev/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/use